<subSubSection id="AB65E39F675280A900F2CE1B95404CE6" pageId="573" pageNumber="574" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="6E95F44E684C5624580AEFEE5917587B" pageId="573" pageNumber="574">
<taxonomicName id="3481DB13300167E9DD5969AB6A93DEBE" authorityName="C.C.A. Zimmermann" authorityYear="1832" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Percosia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="573" pageNumber="574" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Percosia</taxonomicName>
Zimmermann, 1832: 18. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="4E6C97849FBE603E9CDC2AE69AF591C7" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1831" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Amara" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="573" pageNumber="574" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sicula">
<emphasis id="FEAF8B56257E5FC62FE7FECFFA411995" italics="true" pageId="573" pageNumber="574">Amara sicula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Dejean, 1831 designated by Hope (1838: 86). Etymology. Uncertain, possibly from the Latin adjective 
<emphasis id="A135D4F99ED12857054B5DE739ED4995" italics="true" pageId="573" pageNumber="574">percosius</emphasis>
(relative to Percosius, king of Cyzicus an ancient city of Mysia in Asia Minor) [feminine].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DA8D53D35D770D509C82E8B5035BF445" pageId="573" pageNumber="574">
<taxonomicName id="717BCA05899F8397462E23C527EDEF83" authority="Gistel, 1856" authorityName="Gistel" authorityYear="1856" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Spelaeobia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="573" pageNumber="574" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Spelaeobia</taxonomicName>
Gistel, 1856: 358. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="5007D5F601CB002A021255299545E748" authorityName="Duftschmid" authorityYear="1812" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Carabus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="573" pageNumber="574" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="patricius">
<emphasis id="0C1F702C8091019333EEECF7AA3C98F3" italics="true" pageId="573" pageNumber="574">Carabus patricius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Duftschmid, 1812 (= 
<taxonomicName id="BE8E1153AC5D341D5E488C7086BABDD1" authorityName="Duftschmid" authorityYear="1812" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Carabus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="573" pageNumber="574" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="equestris">
<emphasis id="124D632069CFBE08FBAD39143F49E3BD" italics="true" pageId="573" pageNumber="574">Carabus equestris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Duftschmid, 1812) by monotypy. Synonymy established by Bousquet (2002b: 47).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C0516A78F3E95ACA6DB751814914B88D" pageId="573" pageNumber="574" type="diversity">
<paragraph id="F673FE37024678BEE8FF9272ADC71DC9" pageId="573" pageNumber="574">Diversity.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BC9850BC2CC2B574F93F35394194B92D" pageId="573" pageNumber="574">Six species in the boreal and temperate regions of North America (one species), Asia (two species), Europe (three species, two shared with Asia), and northern Africa (two endemic species).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E2D1BC0B144B92CF040E2DD648F919E4" pageId="573" pageNumber="574" type="identification">
<paragraph id="FFE9DC6208404259E2C3662C2295FF3F" pageId="573" pageNumber="574">Identification.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E703E77F590E0406E08BADD80CA8E1BF" pageId="573" pageNumber="574">Hieke (1978) revised the species of this subgenus.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
